    • Uses of IEnvironment in de.stock.environment.types

      Classes in de.stock.environment.types that implement IEnvironment 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Area
      An area is a type of environment and lies in the middle of the environment hierarchy

      Requirements:
      - Its a geographical boundary
      - It must not have a unique proper name

      Typical areas are a forest or a desert
      class  Group
      A group is a type of environment and lies at the very bottom of the environment hierarchy

      Requirements:
      - Its not a geographical boundary
      - Its a part of a location and/or area

      A typical group is cereal
      class  Location
      A location is a type of environment and lies at the very top of the environment hierarchy

      Requirements:
      - Its a geographical boundary
      - It has a unique proper name

      Typical locations are a country like Germany, a confederation like the EU or the Sahara
